        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 3:48AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 348 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Benoit, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winters, Burkett, Dudley, Lawn, Glen Cove, Lake Coleman, Ballinger,
Hatchel, Rowden, Silver Valley, Goldsboro, Ballinger Lake, Novice,
Us-283 Near The Coleman-Callahan County Line, Eula, Echo, Benoit,
Ovalo, Crews, and Valera.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
